headline: Did Revenue Surge and 10 Percent Dividend Hike Just Shift Brown & Brown's (BRO) Investment Narrative?
summary: Brown & Brown, Inc. reported in October 2025 that its third-quarter revenue rose to US$1.61 billion, up from US$1.19 billion a year earlier, exceeding analyst forecasts, while net income for the quarter was US$227 million, slightly below the prior-year period. Alongside its earnings announcement, the company increased its quarterly dividend by 10% to US$0.165 per share, the 32nd consecutive annual increase, and expanded its share buyback authorization by US$1.25 billion, reflecting continued...
